Dorsal pattern . It is quite similar in all these specimens. The number of dorsal blotches varies from 27 to 37 on the body and 5 to 8 on the tail for a total ranging from 35 to 42 . Specimen MNHN 2012.0216 is more distinctly brown than the holotype and lateral blotches are smaller and more irregular. Other elements of the dorsal pattern are similar. In life (
Fig. 5
), upper dorsal surfaces of specimens IEBR A. 2012.6 and ZFMK 93281 were greenishbrown, with dark dorsal blotches, golden in their centre and edged with blackish-brown. In alcohol, the paler center is not as visible and turns to pale greyish-brown.
